data.summary:
divided families usa is a national coalition of volunteers whose vision is to facilitate closure for elderly korean americans who have been separated from their family members in north korea as a result of the korean war. also known as the national coalition for divided families in the past following the release of the divided families documentary in 2014, dfusa seeks to work with the community of first generation korean american divided families to: 

1. advocate for a sustainable system of reunions and exchange of information for first generation korean americans with their direct relatives in north korea;
2. record and archive oral histories of korean american divided families through intergenerational storytelling;
3. account for the demographics of korean american divided families through a private registry.
